NAME: Approach
DESCRIPTION: Approach used for the calculation of capital requirements (or exposure value in LR)

NAME: Accounting standard
DESCRIPTION: The accounting standard used to prepare figures or reports

NAME: Base items
DESCRIPTION:
Defines the basic conceptual meaning of a data point. 
Identifies the framework in which a data point is included. For FINREP, it indicates in which group of element of the financial statement should be included the data point (e.g. assets, liabilities, equity, income, expenses). For COREP, it indicates whether the data point should be computed in the numerator (own funds) or the denominator (exposures) of the Pillar I solvency ratio. 
It may determine whether the data point has a "debit" or a "credit" attribute.

NAME: Boolean total
DESCRIPTION: Dimensions having only two values (usually denoted true and false)

NAME: Covered bond
DESCRIPTION: Name or unambiguous abbreviation of a covered bond issuing entity and the designation of a covered bond

NAME: Collateral/Guarantees
DESCRIPTION: Defines the terms and conditions of the collateral and guarantees

NAME: Contingent scenario
DESCRIPTION: Defines the contingent scenarios whose impact is reported

NAME: Counterparty
DESCRIPTION: Party other than the reporting institution in a contract or transaction.

NAME: Exposure classes
DESCRIPTION: Defines the exposure class for capital requirement purposes

NAME: External ratings
DESCRIPTION: Concepts related with external credit ratings.

NAME: Impairment
DESCRIPTION: Concepts related with monitoring credit quality of financial assets and off-balance sheet items (e.g. past due, impaired, defaulted)

NAME: Legal entity
DESCRIPTION: An association, corporation, partnership, proprietorship, trust, or individual that has legal standing in the eyes of law

NAME: Liquidity
DESCRIPTION: Defines different liquidity-related conditions of assets and liabilities

NAME: Type of market
DESCRIPTION: Defines the type of market on which reported instruments are traded. It includes the fair value hierarchy.

NAME: Main category
DESCRIPTION:
Specifies the nature of the item reported (i.e. answers the question: what is reported?). 
For financial instruments, defines the instrument (e.g. deposits, debt securities issued...) or range of instruments reported. 
It should be defined for each data point.

NAME: Computability in own funds
DESCRIPTION: Specifies the way in which the item computes in own funds

NAME: Portfolio
DESCRIPTION: Defined the portfolios reported. It comprises both accounting portfolios (e.g. Available-for-sale) and prudential portfolios (e.g. trading book).

NAME: Purpose
DESCRIPTION: Purpose of the contract or transaction.

NAME: Reference period
DESCRIPTION: Defines a relative time point (reference date or period) to which the data refers.

NAME: Related parties/Relationships
DESCRIPTION: Defines the relationship between the reporting institution with an entity or a person; in particular, it specifies the type of related party.

NAME: Risk transfer treatment
DESCRIPTION: Type of risk transfer (synthetic or transitional securitisations) and accounting treatment of the transaction

NAME: Scope of consolidation
DESCRIPTION: Different scopes of consolidation of reporting when different from CRR scope

NAME: Securitisation structure
DESCRIPTION: Tranche of the exposure in the securitisation structure

NAME: Security
DESCRIPTION: Financial instrument that represents: an ownership position in a publicly-traded corporation (stock), a creditor relationship with governmental body or a corporation (bond), or rights to ownership as represented by an option.

NAME: Type of activity
DESCRIPTION: Defines the type of activity reported (e.g. asset management or custody)

NAME: Type of risk
DESCRIPTION: Indicates the type of risk arising from exposures or transactions (e.g. credit risk or market risk).

NAME: Code Lists
DESCRIPTION: Codes for use in various metrics

NAME: Fair value option designation
DESCRIPTION: It lists the possible options to irrevocably designate a financial instrument at fair value through profit or loss in accordance with IFRS9

NAME: Type of hedge
DESCRIPTION: Type of Hedge in accordance with the applicable accounting standard and Reg 680/2014 (Annex V)

NAME: To be reclassified to profit or loss
DESCRIPTION: To be reclassified to profit or loss

NAME: consolidation method
DESCRIPTION: The type of consolidtation method used.

NAME: Fair Value Hierarchy
DESCRIPTION: Hierarchy of fair value in accordance with IFRS13

NAME: Type of Risk
DESCRIPTION: Type of risk in accordance with Reg. 680/2014 (Annex V)

NAME: Boolean string
DESCRIPTION:
A Domain that allows string values of TRUE and FALSE only.
Please note that this Domain's purpose is the mapping of non-reference boolean Domains that are not enumerated, e.g. EBA_Boolean.

NAME: Eligible for central bank funding
DESCRIPTION: Domain covering the members: Eligible for central bank funding, Not eligible for central bank funding, Eligible and not eligible for central bank funding and Not applicable.

NAME: Primary asset class of cover pool
DESCRIPTION: Covers the primary asset classes for cover pools according to  Article 129(4) and (5) of Regulation (EU) No 575/2013.

NAME: Credit rating agency
DESCRIPTION:
Credit rating agency used in Asset encumbrance.
See EBA ITS on Asset encumbrance, 5.2.3. Instructions concerning specific columns, External credit rating on covered bond (090-140), As per credit rating agencies' methodology to maintain current external credit rating on covered bond (230-250).

NAME: Level of reporting requested in the specific row of template
DESCRIPTION: Level of reporting requested in the specific row of template

NAME: Statutory covered bond regime
DESCRIPTION:
Statutory covered bond regime information used in Asset encumbrance.
See EBA ITS on Asset encumbrance, 5.2.3. Instructions concerning specific columns, As per the relevant statutory covered bond regime (220).

NAME: High liquidity and credit quality (HQLA) indicator
DESCRIPTION: High liquidity and credit quality (HQLA) indicator

NAME: Asset encumbrance item
DESCRIPTION: Domain comprising Members that allows to distinguish between AE (matching) liability information and AE (underlying) asset / collateral information.

NAME: Available for encumbrance
DESCRIPTION:
Domain covering the members: Available for encumbrance, Not available for encumbrance, Available and not available for encumbrance, Not applicable.
See EBA ITS on Asset encumbrance, 2.2.1. General remarks.

NAME: Retained or bought back instrument
DESCRIPTION: Domain covereing the members: Retained or bought back instrument, Not retained or bought back instrument, Retained and not retained instruments, Not applicable.

NAME: Counterparty role
DESCRIPTION: Role of the counterparties in an instrument.

NAME: Type of protection value
DESCRIPTION: Identification of the type of value provided in the data attribute ‘Protection value’.

NAME: Protection valuation approach
DESCRIPTION: Type of protection valuation; method used to determine the protection value.

NAME: Phase
DESCRIPTION: The phase in the BIRD process.

NAME: Cube type
DESCRIPTION: Specifies the type of cube as part of the data production process.

NAME: Type of scheme
DESCRIPTION: The type of scheme in the BIRD process.

NAME: Type of relationship
DESCRIPTION: The type of relationship between entities.
